translated:
Dahlquist, Sixten Martin, a parish priest (kontraktsprost) in Vretakloster, born on April 2nd, 1888 in Stoby, Kristianstad county, to first traffic inspector Anders D. and Hilda Jönsson. He married Vera Hukén in 1920 and had four children: Harald, born in 1921 and a lieutenant in the L 4 regiment in Linköping, Birgitta born in 1922, Elisabet born in 1924, and Erik born in 1928. 

He completed his Mog:ex. degree in Luleå in 1905 and then obtained his teol. fil. ex. (degree in theology) in 1906, teol. kand. (Bachelor of Theology) in 1910, prakt. teol. ex. (practical theological degree) in 1911 as well as an ex. as a folk school teacher in 1911. He was ordained a priest in the Luleå diocese in 1912. 

He worked as a substitute rector at Murjek's seminary in 1909, a substitute lecturer in Hudiksvall in 1910 and in Luleå in 1913, a curate in Torsåker in 1912, in Nederluleå in 1913, and a relief curate in Åsbo in the same year. He was a headmaster at Boxholm's school in 1914, a vicar in Vretakloster since 1924 and a kontr:prost (dean) in the Gullbergs and Bobergs deanery since 1938. 

He was a member of the board of directors for Linköping's diocese priest's widow home in 1924 and the chairman in 1946, a supplementary member of the cathedral chapter in 1937 and appointed member of the same in 1940. He was a reviewer of the cathedral chapter's finances from 1930-1935, a deputy of the Priesthood Widow and Orphan Fund in 1938-1941, a member of the Swedish clergy support association board of directors in 1941, a church registrar inspector in 1946, an inspector of Linköping's folk school in 1947, and a member of the ASP central board of directors. 

He was also the chairman of the church council and participated in the diocesan council, folk school board, among others. He wrote essays on church and cultural history. He was awarded LNO (The Order of the North Star).
